summary: David Wilkie, the renowned British swimmer and Olympic gold medalist, passed away at the age of 70 after a valiant battle with cancer. His passing has evoked an outpouring of tributes from fellow swimmers, including Sharron Davies, who hailed him as a great in British swimming. name: Paula Vennells
summary: The Post Office Horizon IT Inquiry is investigating the scandal surrounding the Post Office's defective IT system, which resulted in hundreds of innocent sub-postmasters being wrongly convicted of theft and fraud. During the inquiry, former Post Office CEO Paula Vennells has admitted that evidence presented to MPs was inaccurate and that she misled them. Vennells' statements sparked criticism, with some accusing her of "crocodile tears" during her appearance before the inquiry. Despite Vennells' tearful defense, she maintained that she was misled and did not believe there had been any miscarriages of justice. New documents handed over by Vennells before her appearance have raised further questions about her involvement in the scandal. The inquiry is ongoing, and Vennells is expected to face tough questioning about her role in the Post Office's IT system failures and the subsequent miscarriage of justice.

Industry experts speculate on Nvidia's potential competition and the trajectory of its stock value over the next year. Startups are emerging to challenge Nvidia's dominance, while established companies like Northrop Grumman are partnering with Nvidia to enhance their AI capabilities. These headlines collectively demonstrate Nvidia's significant impact on the tech industry and its continuous evolution in the face of market dynamics.

name: Keir Starmer
summary: Keir Starmer, the leader of the Labour Party in the United Kingdom, has unveiled his party's election strategy, focusing on six "first steps" if Labour wins the upcoming general election. These steps include actions such as freezing energy prices, increasing the minimum wage, and raising taxes on the wealthy. Despite low personal popularity, Starmer remains a contender for the position of Prime Minister. However, he warns that it may take up to ten years to address the "mess" created by the Conservative government. Critics have mixed reactions to Starmer's pledges, with some comparing him to former Prime Minister Tony Blair.

name: RCB vs RR
summary: In the IPL 2024 Eliminator, the Rajasthan Royals (RR) secured a stunning four-wicket victory over the Royal Challengers Bangalore (RCB), knocking RCB out of the tournament. With six balls remaining, RR chased down RCB's total, setting up a Knockout clash with the Sunrisers Hyderabad (SRH). The match witnessed a brilliant performance by Rovman Powell, whose six sealed the victory for RR. In the lead-up to the match, pundits were eagerly predicting the outcome, with Sunil Gavaskar suggesting RR could dominate the game. The victory marks RR's continued success against RCB in the playoffs, having previously eliminated them in the 2024 season.

name: Ten Hag
summary: Erik ten Hag, Manchester United's manager, has expressed optimism about the team's progress despite ongoing speculation about his future. Ten Hag believes the club is in a better position than it was a year ago. However, his job is reportedly in jeopardy, with rumors of a "tug of war" between European clubs who expect his dismissal. Sources indicate that Man Utd will consider replacing him with Mauricio Pochettino if current Chelsea-bound Graham Potter becomes available. Despite the absence of Champions League football next season, Ten Hag maintains that United remains attractive to potential players. However, critics have called for his sacking, and Rio Ferdinand predicts his departure after the FA Cup Final.

name: Steve Wright
summary: Steve Wright, a former Norwich landlord, has been charged with the murder of 17-year-old Victoria Hall in 1999. Hall's body was found in woodland near Ipswich, Suffolk, in 2000. Wright was also charged with the attempted kidnap of another woman in June 2000. These charges come 24 years after Hall's murder, and over a year after Wright's death in December 2022. Meanwhile, an inquest into the death of a different Steve Wright, the BBC Radio 2 DJ who passed away in August 2022, has been closed without an inquest.
